ng\u003Epressure\u003C/strong\u003E sensation is carried by the anterior (ventral) spinothalamic tract, along with crude touch sensation. It is a component of the anterolateral system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPain\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Etemperature\u003C/strong\u003E sensations are carried by the lateral spinothalamic tract\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFine touch\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Evibration\u003C/strong\u003E sensations are carried in the dorsal column-medial lemniscal pathway\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior spinothalamic tract decussates at the anterior white commissure, approximately 1-2 segments above the level of entry, and ascends to the thalamus on the contralateral side.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anterior spinothalamic tract transmits crude touch and pressure information to the thalamus.","The lateral spinothalamic tract transmits pain and temperature information to the thalamus.","Fine touch and vibration sensations are carried by the dorsal column-medial lemniscal pathway."],"references":["Al-Chalabi M, Reddy V, Gupta S. Neuroanatomy, Spinothalamic Tract. 2023 Aug 14. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29939601.","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61270"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16825"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61270